
Overview of noun pardon

The noun pardon has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) forgiveness, pardon -- (the act of excusing a mistake or offense)
2. pardon, amnesty -- (a warrant granting release from punishment for an offense)
3. amnesty, pardon, free pardon -- (the formal act of liberating someone)

Overview of verb pardon

The verb pardon has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (2) excuse, pardon -- (accept an excuse for; "Please excuse my dirty hands")
2. (2) pardon -- (grant a pardon to; "Ford pardoned Nixon"; "The Thanksgiving turkey was pardoned by the President")
